{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016F7TzA1mS3EuWMqyz9Bth2","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of my findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've completed a thorough search of the workspace for documentation and code related to evolution, fitness, and pareto concepts. Here are my findings:\n\n### Documentation Files Found\n\n1. **Main Architecture Documents:**\n   - `/workspace/CLAUDE.md` - Project overview with Hexagonal architecture diagram showing `internal/domain/`, `internal/ports/`, and `internal/adapters/` structure\n   - `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md` - Full system design document describing three binaries (cloche, cloched, cloche-agent)\n\n2. **Evolution-Related Documentation:**\n   - `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md` - **Primary evolution design doc** (459 lines)\n     - Describes multi-stage pipeline: Collector → Classifier → Reflector → Executor branches\n     - Details three executor branches: Prompt Curator, Script Generator, DSL Mutator\n     - Covers knowledge base structure, audit logging, and trigger logic\n     - **Does NOT mention fitness or pareto** directly in the design\n   \n   - `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md` - Implementation plan for evolution system (67KB)\n     - Step-by-step tasks for implementing the evolution pipeline\n     - References internal package structure extensively\n     - **Does NOT mention fitness or pareto**\n\n3. **Other Relevant Design Docs:**\n   - `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md` - References `internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`\n\n### Code Found (Not Previously Documented)\n\n**Two new files exist in the git status (untracked):**\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/fitness.go` - **NEW fitness metrics implementation**\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/fitness_test.go` - **NEW fitness test suite**\n\n**Key Functions in fitness.go:**\n- `EvaluateRun()` - Extracts fitness metrics (success, retry count, duration) from a `domain.Run`\n- `RecordFitness()` - Persists FitnessRecord to JSONL file\n- `LoadFitness()` - Reads FitnessRecords from JSONL\n- `AggregateFitness()` - Groups records by candidate, computes success rate and efficiency\n- `Dominates()` - **Pareto dominance comparison** between two candidates\n- `ComputeParetoFront()` - **Computes Pareto frontier** from candidates\n- `FitnessPath()` - Returns conventional JSONL path: `.cloche/evolution/fitness/<workflow>.jsonl`\n\n**Internal Evolution Package Structure:**\n```\n/workspace/internal/evolution/\n├── fitness.go (NEW)\n├── fitness_test.go (NEW)\n├── classifier.go\n├── collector.go\n├── curator.go\n├── orchestrator.go\n├── reflector.go\n├── scriptgen.go\n├── audit.go\n├── trigger.go\n├── llmclient.go\n├── types.go\n└── [various test files]\n```\n\n### Key Findings\n\n1. **Evolution package exists** in `/workspace/internal/evolution/` with 16 files implementing the full pipeline described in the design doc\n2. **Fitness and Pareto concepts are NOT documented** in any `.md` files but are **newly implemented** in `fitness.go`\n3. **Pareto frontier concept is present** - `ComputeParetoFront()` and `Dominates()` functions implement multi-objective optimization (success rate vs efficiency)\n4. **Fitness metrics structure:** Success rate (% of runs that succeeded) and Efficiency (1 / (1 + avgRetries + avgDurationSeconds/60))\n5. **No GEPA references** found anywhere in the codebase\n6. **Fitness data persists** to `.cloche/evolution/fitness/<workflow>.jsonl` in JSONL format\n\n### File Paths Summary\n\n**Documentation:**\n- `/workspace/CLAUDE.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`\n\n**Code (Evolution + Fitness):**\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/fitness.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/fitness_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/` (16 total files)\n\n**Related Design Docs:**\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md`\n\nThe fitness and pareto implementations appear to be recently added features that extend the self-evolution system described in the design documents, enabling multi-objective optimization for workflow candidates."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7be5fb9570d06316 (use SendMessage with to: 'a7be5fb9570d06316' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 44015\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 30791</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a2c49b8d-da70-4500-b77a-712a3c934288","uuid":"d4b9c6b2-85d9-46d1-8b93-a976928dcd6f","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:11:41.686Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search the /workspace directory for any documentation files (*.md, docs/) that mention \"evolution\", \"fitness\", \"pareto\", or \"GEPA\". Also check the project layout documentation in CLAUDE.md and any docs/ directory for architecture docs that describe the internal/ package structure. I need to know which docs exist and whether they reference the evolution package. Return file paths and relevant content snippets.","agentId":"a7be5fb9570d06316","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of my findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've completed a thorough search of the workspace for documentation and code related to evolution, fitness, and pareto concepts. Here are my findings:\n\n### Documentation Files Found\n\n1. **Main Architecture Documents:**\n   - `/workspace/CLAUDE.md` - Project overview with Hexagonal architecture diagram showing `internal/domain/`, `internal/ports/`, and `internal/adapters/` structure\n   - `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md` - Full system design document describing three binaries (cloche, cloched, cloche-agent)\n\n2. **Evolution-Related Documentation:**\n   - `/workspace